    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-27T04:54:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-27T04:54:00-05:00" n="757"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51A/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moose</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-27T13:00:00+03:06"
                            >April 27, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 28—9:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>123. Authorization to mention advisers contained in Department’s 69, April 25, 8
                    p.m. received after my return to Jidda. Substance of Department’s message will
                    be conveyed to King at first favorable opportunity.</p>
                <p>Suggestion of military adviser would be presented under more favorable
                    circumstances if Department authorized me to say that President is ready to
                    appoint adviser should King so desire.</p>
                <p>Colonel Eddy arrived at King’s camp; he is probably in Riyadh today and intends
                    to reach Baghdad May 5 after visiting Dhahran; he is ready to return to Riyadh
                    any time needed there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
